      #What’s wrong with existing careers advice for people who want to make an impact?

      1. [5 common pieces of advice that don’t work.](http://80000hours.org/blog/183-the-worst-ethical-careers-advice-in-the-world) Perhaps it’s better to [“do what’s valuable”](http://80000hours.org/blog/187-the-best-career-advice-you-ll-never-hear-in-a-graduation-speech).

      2. Many common ways to make a difference don’t clearly work, like [microfinance](http://80000hours.org/blog/123-is-microcredit-mostly-hype) or [building schools](http://80000hours.org/blog/100-let-s-stop-building-schools), and it’s [difficult to work out which do](http://80000hours.org/blog/66-social-interventions-gone-wrong).

      3. The impact of different paths can [vary massively](http://80000hours.org/blog/94-how-to-do-one-year-of-work-in-four-hours), but people rarely try to assess the impact of different options.

      4. We often don’t consider [what would have happened](http://80000hours.org/blog/112-what-s-your-true-impact) if we hadn’t acted. Some people who think they are doing good are probably doing harm instead.

